<item>
            <title>[DATAMONGO-571] Spring Data for MongoDb doesn&apos;t save null values when @Version is added to domain class </title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-571</link>
                <project id="10701" key="DATAMONGO">Spring Data MongoDB</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Scenario:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Domain class is loaded from mongodb using &lt;tt&gt;CrudRepository.findOne(&#8230;)&lt;/tt&gt; method.&lt;br/&gt;
2. The loaded instance&#8217;s any non &lt;tt&gt;id&lt;/tt&gt; nor &lt;tt&gt;@Version&lt;/tt&gt; annotated field is set to &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;br/&gt;
3. The loaded instance is saved to same mongodb using &lt;tt&gt;CrudRepository.save(&#8230;)&lt;/tt&gt; method.&lt;br/&gt;
4. The field that has been set to &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt; doesn&#8217;t write to database, it&#8217;s unchanged.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Important: The problem doesn&#8217;t occur when &lt;tt&gt;@Version&lt;/tt&gt; annotation is not used in the domain class definition.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
